comments.author: @이종수-w4t
comments.comment:
간통보다 더 악한 범죄는?


악은 간통행위에 대해 죄를 묻지 않는다.


악에 대한 도발은 바로 악이 장악한  영역을 회복하고 해방하려는 살아서 선의 영역을 회복하려는 사람이다.


악에 대한 치명적인 적대 행위는 분리수거다.


분리수거는 양심을 회복하고 바른 사고력을 갖고 바른 삶을 살고자 하는 사람이다.


악이 선의 영역을 무단 침입하고 악의 힘을 빌어 영역을 확장하고 세상을 정복하고 축재한 자들로 하여금 악의 하수인으로 지구 인류 전체를 죽음과 파멸로 유인하고자 하는 계락을 무위로 돌리고 광명의 세상을 회복시키려는 광복 해방운동을 저지시키려는 의인들을 탄압하던 정복자들의 만행은 머지 않은 짧은 근대역사를 봐서도 알 수 있다.


분리수거는 하나님의 심정을 상속받고 그 소중함을 알고 실천하는 살아 있는 사람의 증거다.

그러나 양두구육에 인면수심에 겉으로는 신앙생활을 하지만 하나님과 소통하지 않고 구습과 구틀과 흙탕물의 세속과 영합하여 낫 놓고 기역자도 모르고 손발로 신앙하지 않고 머리와 입으로 신앙하는 세상의 잣대와 질시와 안목이 두려워  분리수거의 소중함을 모르고 이행하지 않는 봉건 농경 문화시대의 고정관념의 신앙으로 자원을 가용하여 생활하는 과학문명시대에 몸을 굴리며 신앙생활을 하는 사람이다.


분리수거의 미 이행은 하나님의 천지운행을 파괴,

붕괴시키는 하나님의 천법을 파괴하는 형사적으로 구속당해야 하는 중대한 현행범과 같다.


당연히 그런 행위를 하는 신앙자의 믿음은 헛돌고 겉도는 불량한 위선적 행위다.


가난한 나라에선 돈이 없어 생계가 어려우면 자녀를 매음굴에 팔거나 부자집에 거액으로 애첩으로 팔고 윤락으로 생계를 유지한다.


말하고자 하는 가난함이란?


자원의 고갈이다.


현존 인류와 미래세대의 잇는 생존터전은 자원이다.


이것이 부족해지면 현대과학문명의 이기로 치루는 전쟁은 과거의 무기와 판이하게 다른 지구 전체를 몰살하고 초토화 시키는 아비규환의 지옥이다.


분리수거의 미 이행은 천국을 지옥으로 갉아 먹는 도저히 용서가 안되는 범죄 행위다.


이 중대한 범죄를 망각시켜 

사필귀정 인과응보 자업자득의 응징의 처벌을 무감각함으로

죽음직전으로 올가미를 걸고 몰고 가고자 하는 마약으로 극단의 이기심과 극단의 경쟁심을 부추겨서 만사 제쳐 놓고 재물축적에 혈안이 되고 몰입시키는 것은 황금만능의 현행제도의 모순과 금덩어리다.


이기적인 기득권들이 자신들의 이익을 고수하고 수성하기 위해 국수주의의 틀을 공고히 하는 블록화하는 것은 세계평화를 막고 방해하고 파멸을 가속화시키는 난공불락의 장애물이다.


 그 누구의 탓도 이니다.


주인이 발등에 떨어져야 반응하는 구태와 구습의 습성으로 안주하며 양심과 지조의 주인정신을 헌신짝 버리듯이 자리를 잃는데서 비롯된다.


한 개인이 천하를 바꿀 수는 없지만  그러나 자신의 굳은 결심과 의지로  자신을 지키고 살리기 위해 노력하는 일이다.


첫술에 배부르지 않는다. 


 눈에 보이지 않는 씨앗이 자라 감히 넘볼 수 없는 유전인자라는 미래의 자신을 계획하고 성장시키려는 노력이 세상을 살리는 길이다.


불확실한 현실에 생명보전이 최우선이듯이

마음(선의와 사고력)을 죽이지 않고 온전히 자신을 주관하도록 향상을 위해 부단히 노력하는 것이다.


민주주의 세상의 주인은 당신이다.

소비자는 왕이요 시청자는 왕이요 국민주권자는 왕이라 이 기반의 주인이 자신의 자리에 대한 소중함을 잃고 저버려서 뿌리 없는 물처럼 비롯됨으로 물위에 뜬 위정자들은 당신이 흔들리는데로 흔들리고 요동치고 세상이 죽는 것이다.


세상이 아무리 무탈하고 풍족해도 당신이 그 가치를 모르면 죽음처럼 무의미하고 황폐한 것이다.

comments.author: @INCHRISTENDTIMES
comments.comment:
My Friend: I am asking you the most important question of life. Your joy or your sorrow for all eternity
depends upon your answer. The question is: Are you saved? It is not a question of how good you are, nor if
you are a church member, but are you saved? Are you sure you will go to Heaven when you die?
God says in order to go to Heaven, you must be born again. In John 3:7, Jesus said to Nicodemus, “Ye must be
born again.”
In the Bible God gives us the plan of how to be born again which means to be saved. His plan is simple! You
can be saved today. How?
First, my friend, you must realize you are a sinner. “For all have sinned, and come short of the glory of God”
(Romans 3:23).
Because you are a sinner, you are condemned to death. “For the wages [payment] of sin is death” (Romans
6:23). This includes eternal separation from God in Hell.
“ . . . it is appointed unto men once to die, but after this the judgment” (Hebrews 9:27).
But God loved you so much He gave His only begotten Son, Jesus, to bear your sin and die in your place.
“ . . . He hath made Him [Jesus, Who knew no sin] to be sin for us . . . that we might be made the righteousness
of God in Him” (2 Corinthians 5:21).
Jesus had to shed His blood and die. “For the life of the flesh is in the blood” (Lev. 17:11). “ . . . without
shedding of blood is no remission [pardon]” (Hebrews 9:22).
“ . . . God commendeth His love toward us, in that, while we were yet sinners, Christ died for us.”
(Romans 5:8).
Although we cannot understand how, God said my sins and your sins were laid upon Jesus and He died in our
place. He became our substitute. It is true. God cannot lie.
My friend, “God . . . commandeth all men everywhere to repent” (Acts 17:30). This repentance is a change of
mind that agrees with God that one is a sinner, and also agrees with what Jesus did for us on the Cross.
In Acts 16:30-31, the Philippian jailer asked Paul and Silas: “ . . . ‘Sirs, what must I do to be saved?’ And they
said, ‘Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ, and thou shalt be saved . . . .’ ”
Simply believe on Him as the one who bore your sin, died in your place, was buried, and whom God
resurrected. His resurrection powerfully assures that the believer can claim everlasting life when Jesus is
received as Savior.
“But as many as received Him, to them gave He power to become the sons of God, even to them that believe
on His name” (John 1:12).
“For whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.” (Romans 10:13).
Whosoever includes you. Shall be saved means not maybe, nor can, but shall be saved.
Surely, you realize you are a sinner. Right now, wherever you are, repenting, lift your heart to God in prayer.
In Luke 18:13, the sinner prayed: “God be merciful to me a sinner.” Just pray: “Oh God, I know I am a sinner.
I believe Jesus was my substitute when He died on the Cross. I believe His shed blood, death, burial, and
resurrection were for me. I now receive Him as my Savior. I thank You for the forgiveness of my sins, the gift
of salvation and everlasting life, because of Your merciful grace. Amen.”
Just take God at His word and claim His salvation by faith. Believe, and you will be saved. No church, no
lodge, no good works can save you. Remember, God does the saving. All of it!
God’s simple plan of salvation is: You are a sinner. Therefore, unless you believe on Jesus Who died in your
place, you will spend eternity in Hell. If you believe on Him as your crucified, buried, and risen Savior, you
receive forgiveness for all of your sins and His gift of eternal salvation by faith.
You say, “Surely, it cannot be that simple.” Yes, that simple! It is scriptural. It is God’s plan. My friend, believe
on Jesus and receive Him as Savior today.
If His plan is not perfectly clear, read this tract over and over, without laying it down, until you understand
it. Your soul is worth more than all the world.
“For what shall it profit a man, if he shall gain the whole world and lose his own soul?” (Mark 8:36).
Be sure you are saved. If you lose your soul, you miss Heaven and lose all. Please! Let God save you this very
moment.
God’s power will save you, keep you saved, and enable you to live a victorious Christian life. “There hath no
temptation taken you but such as is common to man: but God is faithful, Who will not suffer you to be tempted
above that ye are able; but will with the temptation also make a way to escape, that ye may be able to bear it” (1
Corinthians 10:13).
Do not trust your feelings. They change. Stand on God’s promises. They never change. After you are saved,
there are three things to practice daily for spiritual growth:
Pray -- you talk to God.
Read your Bible -- God talks to you.
Witness -- you talk for God.
You should be baptized in obedience to the Lord Jesus Christ as a public testimony of your salvation, and
then unite with a Bible-believing church without delay. “Be not thou therefore ashamed of the testimony of
our Lord . . . .” (2 Timothy 1:8)
“Whosoever therefore shall confess [testify of] Me before men, him will I confess also before My Father which
is in heaven”

How we choose to respond to life make a positive impact.

If Trump lies, be honest and truthful.
If Trump takes extreme action, take a middle path of wise action.
If Trump acts illegally, act legally.
If Trump further divides the world, unite the world in your community.
If Trump blames unfairly, take fully responsibility for ourselves and be fair.
If Trump ignores climate science, respect and share credible climate science with all people.
If Trump acts ignorantly, learn from credible, diverse sources and understand.
If Trump only cares about the wealthy and powerful, care about all people.
If Trump tries to incite more violence, be mindful of feelings and act with mutual respect.
If Trump tries to encourage more conspiracy theories, think critically about all theories and choose mindfully.
If Trump only inserts his friends in key positions in government, review all candidates and hire those who are most qualified and motivated to serve in your business and community.
If Trump only acts in his and his elite friend's interests, act in everyone's interest.
If Trump doesn't work to resolve global wars, conflicts and tensions, then work to build mutual respect, understanding and peace in your family, community and workplace.
If Trump misuses funds, use funds responsibly at all times.
If Trump allows for conflicts of interest with business, ensure that every piece of business you do is ethical, fair and respectful for all people, and of the law.
If Trump marginalises the planet that supports our lives and wealth, reduce your and your business' environmental impact.
If Trump only serves his party at the expense of the whole country, vote for those who are better than him.
If Trump does something positive, appreciate it.
If Trump holds himself accountable, praise it.

Regardless of what Trump does or doesn't do, act with integrity, authenticity, humility, understanding, respect, peace and generosity for all people.

comments.author: @OmniphonProductions
comments.comment:
"The Golden Age of America begins right now," because his policies will continue to favor wealthy men in their golden years. Talking about a crisis of trust, weaponization of government, the radical establishment (contradiction of terms) extracting wealth and power from our citizens, denial of liberty, inflation, the national debt, constitutional rule of law, respect, ending fascism, and being, "...tested and challenged more than any president in our 250-year history," all reveals he is either the most dishonest man in America, or the least self-aware. Even after winning a second (last) term, he's still lying, selling his brand, because if he told the truth, his acolytes would stop buying his merchandise.

"Make America Great Again," implies that America's greatest days lie sometime in the past. Anyone who believes that, either lacks imagination or relies exclusively on it!
America has yet to realize it's full potential, and policies that inhibit...or even roll back..."Liberty and Justice for all," can only serve to deter making America greater!

As for Trump's, "...mandate," and claim of, "...unification," behind the Republican Agenda, the majority of voters didn't vote for him. He won a plurality of the popular vote, beating Harris by less than 2% of the total vote count, but between Harris, RFK Jr., and other third party or write-in candidates, the collective majority of Americans voted for somebody other than Trump. He received more votes than any other individual candidate, and he won the Electoral College. He is the President, but a unified mandate...no!

Regarding the, "Revolution of Common Sense," it's important to remember that any individual's notion of Common Sense is reflective of their own level of education and life experience. Common Sense is a phrase people use when they mean, "In accordance with my own preconceptions," which often rooted in willful, self-serving ignorance! When Trump said, "I love the poorly educated," it wasn't a compliment; it was because poorly educated (or systematically mis-educated) people tend to be more gullible! On a related note, I would have thought that a man with a Bachelor's Degree in Economics would understand how tariff's and deficit spending actually work...or don't work!

I will give him credit for one thing. He's guaranteed to fulfill some campaign promises! Ending the federal policies of, "...trying to socially engineer race and gender into every aspect of public and private life," or subjecting military personnel to, "...radical political theories and social experiments," will be easy to do. Just don't do the thing that already isn't being done...like targeting innocent political opponents for unjustified prosecution. Meanwhile, he'll reinstate military personnel who objected to the COVID vaccine, while again expelling military service personnel for being LGBTQ+ (violating Title VII of the Civil Rights Act, according to the very same Supreme Court he stacked). Speaking of the military, will our success also be measured by the wars we don't promote by emboldening foreign leaders who would attack and oppress their neighbors (and own citizens)?

HOW DARE HE take credit for the release of the hostages in Gaza as though he had anything to do with those months-long negotiations, especially after (as just mentioned) emboldening a regime that continues to systematically oppress an already marginalized demographic group to the point of violent response...only for that same regime then use that violence as an excuse to spend more than a year killing tens of thousands of civilians, more than half of whom were children.

As for the Gulf of Mexico, Denali, and the Panama Canal, his policies will (1) do absolutely nothing to improve life for Americans and/or (2) violate international law. As pertains to my second paragraph, returning things to how they used to be...just because they used to be that way...isn't just a waste of energy; it's illegal in many cases. We can't take back the Panama Canal (or annex Greenland) without committing an act of war. Changing the names of geographic features won't affect the price of gas or groceries, but it will require educational institutions to spend money on updated textbooks! How much will it cost taxpayers to replace History and Geography texts in every public school, and what's the point if every other nation in the world is not obligated or legally compelled to acknowledge the changes anyway? Wasted money, wasted energy, wasted air!

Hearing him utter the phrase, "Manifest Destiny," literally turned my stomach. Considering how many millions of people have died because of that philosophy, why does anyone think America needs to, "...increase our territory," when so many of our current citizens don't have adequate food, shelter, or medical care. If you want to make America great, direct your own billions at that problem...and implore your fellow billionaires to do the same...before spending our tax dollars economic imperialism. What's the point of, "...growing your business," if the employees you already have can't pay their bills?

Side Note: It's incredibly revealing to see members of self-described news organizations in the audience...not with cameras, microphones, notepads, or a shred of journalistic integrity, but as sycophantic propagandists whose networks have paid hundreds of millions of dollars in penalties for knowingly perpetuating lies on his behalf!

I genuinely hope his presidency proves successful for the American people. Unfortunately history indicates that his primary...if not only...priority is himself.

comments.author: @amicableamerica
comments.comment:
One day soon, those who originally stood truth to power during Don's first term (and beyond), but who are now yielding to fear or self-interest, may come to regret their inaction.

I am deeply disappointed in America today.

I haven't felt this disheartened by America since Bush and his legion of minions silenced the true and accurate majority of voices in 2000.

Personally, I still question the events of 9/11. How might the world have unfolded differently if Gore had been where he was rightfully meant to be?

Don has frightened, bullied, manipulated, bribed, and bought his way back into the very House he turned upside down and inside out during his first term.

How is that different from what happened in 2000? If it's not, what might lie ahead for America?

Those of us who are attuned to reality already know that our system has devolved into a hodgepodge of oligarchy, autocracy, plutocracy, and theocracy, with millionaire and billionaire technocrats—who have major stakes in the game—helping to make the key decisions.

Am I forgetting anything?

Oh yes, democratic governance. It's still limping along for now, but how long will that last if the complete militarization and securitization of government take hold?

If that happens, what then? Will pesky journalists, dissenters, and members of Congress start showing up poisoned? Accidentally falling from windows? Perhaps the troublesome ones will simply vanish, with no fuss and no mess.

In his first term, Don boasted that he could shoot people in broad daylight and not lose a single vote. Recently, he subtly incited his mysterious group of willing extremists to shoot through crowds of journalists. You know, those shadowy figures who don't exist—until they somehow materialize.

It's a chilling reality that we've become numb to the implications of his rhetoric. As the walls close in, those who once held power in the name of democracy now stand silent, complicit, or too afraid to speak out. The lines between fact and fiction, between right and wrong, are so blurred that it's hard to discern where the truth lies anymore.

And so, we find ourselves in a precarious position, questioning not only our present but our future as well. Will we continue down this path, or will the voices of reason and justice rise again before it's too late? The answer remains uncertain, but one thing is clear: the stakes have never been higher. The future of America, and perhaps the world, hinges on the choices we make in the coming days. Will we reclaim the ideals that once defined us, or will we succumb to the forces that seek to dismantle everything we hold dear? The time to act is now.

video_details.title: Anti Trump Protest LIVE | Donald Trump Latest News | 50 States Protest In US Hill Capitol LIVE |N18G
video_details.description:
In mid-February, thousands of people across the United States mobilized in opposition to President Trump and Elon Musk’s attempts to bring nonpartisan and independent government institutions under their personal control. These demonstrations received substantial coverage in major media, as have recent town hall meetings at which constituents have demanded action from their representatives in Congress. This turnout and coverage were undoubtedly gratifying to organizers, but the nascent movement is not yet supported by a media infrastructure adequate to build long-term momentum.

comments.comment: Instead of firing federal employees, every federal worker should have a five-year job cycle. Additionally, any U.S. citizen should have the opportunity to participate in a similar five-year job cycle within the public sector. If someone holds a permanent job for 40 years, the system itself restricts growth and competition because the government, unlike private companies, never faces bankruptcy. This is why private-sector employees continuously work, learn, and update their skills—otherwise, they risk losing their jobs. Implementing a five-year working cycle would benefit everyone, ensuring adaptability and progress.

video_details.title: Donald Trump asks Keir Starmer if UK can take on Russia by itself
video_details.description:
The US president, Donald Trump, equivocated when asked whether the US would come to the aid of British troops potentially deployed to Ukraine.
Subscribe to Guardian News on YouTube ► http://bit.ly/guardianwiressub

Trump said the British could 'take care of themselves very well' and praised the UK army. He then said if the UK needed help, 'I'll always be with the British, I'll always be with them'. After the awkward interaction, Trump asked the UK prime minister, Keir Starmer, whether the UK could 'take on Russia by yourselves' before bursting into laughter

In some cultures and situations, crossing your legs while sitting can be interpreted as a sign of disrespect, particularly when in the presence of someone older or of higher status, as it can be seen as a casual or relaxed posture that may not convey proper attentiveness; however, this perception varies greatly depending on cultural norms and the context of the situation. 

Key points about crossing legs and respect:

Cultural differences:

Certain cultures, like Japan, consider crossing legs as disrespectful, especially when sitting in front of someone older or more respected. 

Power dynamics:

In some professional settings, crossing legs might be interpreted as a power move, indicating confidence or dominance, but can also be seen as dismissive depending on the situation. 

Formal settings:

In formal situations, like meetings with superiors or religious ceremonies, keeping legs uncrossed is often considered more appropriate.

comments.comment:
The concept of a Russian world order and the implications of a BRICS currency on a global scale are complex and multifaceted topics. The BRICS nations, comprising Brazil, Russia, India, China, and South Africa, have been seeking to establish a more multipolar world order, with a greater emphasis on cooperation and mutual benefit among emerging economies 1.

One of the key objectives of the BRICS bloc is to reduce its reliance on the US dollar and promote the use of local currencies in international trade 2. This has led to discussions about the possibility of establishing a BRICS currency, which could potentially challenge the dominance of the US dollar in global trade 3.

However, the creation of a BRICS currency would require significant political and economic compromises among the member states, including the establishment of a banking union, a fiscal union, and macroeconomic convergence 2. Despite these challenges, a united BRICS currency could boost trade and global influence among the member states, while also reducing their reliance on the US dollar 3.

The BRICS economies already account for a significant share of global gross domestic product, with an estimated 37.3% based on purchasing power parity 4. China alone is a major driver of global economic growth, and its economic influence is likely to continue to grow in the coming years 4.

A stronger BRICS+ could have a significant global impact in various areas, including energy, trade networks, infrastructure, monetary policy, and technology 5. The establishment of a BRICS currency could also contribute to a more diversified and stable global financial system, reducing the risks associated with a single dominant currency 6.

However, the use of local currencies in international trade is still limited, and the US dollar remains the dominant currency in global commodity trade 8. To overcome this challenge, the BRICS nations would need to develop a more robust and integrated financial system, with a strong and stable currency that can compete with the US dollar 9.

In the aftermath of the 2009 Yekaterinburg summit, the BRIC nations announced the need for a new global reserve currency, which would have to be "diverse, stable, and predictable" 10. While the idea of a BRICS currency is still in its infancy, it has the potential to contribute to a more multipolar world order, with a greater emphasis on cooperation and mutual benefit among emerging economies 1.

Information is missing on the specific details of the proposed BRICS currency, including its design, implementation, and potential impact on global trade and finance. Further research and analysis are needed to fully understand the implications of a BRICS currency on a global scale.


Since the 2nd world war comes to an end of capitalization perhaps books that explore the concept of a post-capitalist society. Here are a few notable ones:

"Das Kapital" by Karl Marx: While not directly about the end of capitalization, this book is a foundational critique of capitalism and explores the idea of a socialist or communist alternative.

"The End of History and the Last Man" by Francis Fukuyama: This book doesn't specifically argue for the end of capitalization but explores the idea that liberal democracy and free-market capitalism might be the final form of human government, marking the end of history as we know it.

"PostCapitalism: A Guide to Our Future" by Paul Mason: Mason argues that the current form of capitalism is coming to an end due to technological advancements and offers a vision of a post-capitalist future.

"The Zero Marginal Cost Society" by Jeremy Rifkin: Rifkin explores how the Internet of things and other technological changes could lead to a nearly free economy, potentially undermining traditional capitalist structures.

"Utopia for Realists: And How We Can Get There" by Rutger Bregman: While not exclusively focused on the end of capitalization, Bregman discusses various utopian ideas, including a universal basic income, which could significantly alter how we think about work and wealth.

"Doughnut Economics: Seven Ways to Think Like a 21st-Century Economist" by Kate Raworth: Raworth challenges traditional economic thinking, including aspects of capitalism, and proposes a new model that prioritizes human well-being and environmental sustainability.

These books offer a range of perspectives on the future of capitalism and potential alternatives. They're a good starting point for anyone interested in exploring these ideas further.

The Gulf of Mexico has had its name for centuries, with the term "Gulf of Mexico" being used since at least the early 16th century. The name likely originates from the Spanish term "Golfo de México," referring to the region's connection to the ancient Mexican civilization and its proximity to the country. The Gulf was explored by early Spanish explorers like Hernán Cortés, and its name became more widely used after European exploration and mapping of the region.

So, the Gulf of Mexico has had its name for around 500 years.

comments.author: @asitis4826
comments.comment:
After reading this, it looks like the Panama Canal is better if it was really was in chinas hands.

China does not manage or control the Panama Canal, but it has significant economic involvement and influence related to it. Here are the key points regarding China's connection to the Panama Canal:

Commercial Ties:
Chinese companies are among the largest users of the Panama Canal. The canal is critical for China's trade with the Americas, as it provides a faster route for shipping goods between Asia and the east coasts of North and South America.
A considerable portion of the cargo passing through the canal is either destined for or originates from China.

Port Operations:
Chinese companies have investments in port facilities near the Panama Canal. For example, China’s Hutchison Ports operates ports on both ends of the canal: in Balboa on the Pacific side and in Colón on the Atlantic side. These ports play a critical role in transshipment and logistics.

Panama-China Relations:
In 2017, Panama severed diplomatic ties with Taiwan and established formal relations with China. Since then, China has become a significant economic partner for Panama, engaging in trade, infrastructure projects, and investments.

Infrastructure Projects:
Chinese companies have shown interest in infrastructure projects in Panama, including proposals to build or modernize railways, highways, and ports. Some of these projects have been linked to China's Belt and Road Initiative (BRI), which aims to expand China's global trade and influence.

No Direct Control of the Canal

Despite these ties, the Panama Canal Authority (ACP) retains full control over the canal's operation. China's influence is primarily economic and strategic, rather than administrative or operational.
